        <p>Taylor CC Services was formed in late 2006 by Ian Taylor as a response to an increasing need for PLC programmers with a broad understanding of oil and gas process systems. After achieving success in process troubleshooting, network design and programming, Taylor CC Services expanded to also provide logistics and panel fabrication.</p>

        <p>In early 2009, Taylor CC Services became Connect Control Systems Inc. and Ian took the role of President. This new direction was a response to increased client needs for further support and development in project management, process, data acquisition, communications, engineering, troubleshooting and field services.</p>

        <p>Connect Control Systems has been able to achieve healthy exponential growth and has recently expanded by opening two key divisions: Connect Global Corp. which is focused on supporting the expanding oil and gas industry in the USA and a Control Panel Fabrication shop supplying automation products in various industrial applications. Along with these two areas Connect Control Systems has sustained its original focus of providing automation services across Alberta in Edmonton, Fort St. John, Grande Prairie, and Hinton.</p>
